From 3e6d60dc7ad759fe6a9c64bfad4fa1866597a1cb Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Slick <slick@slicksync.local>
Date: Sun, 12 Jul 2026 06:53:41 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] feat: softer Slick theme, add Velvet + Lagoon themes, fix
 provider badge colors

Slick's original violet/cyan combo (#a855f7 / #22d3ee) was too high-
saturation/neon. Replaced with softer periwinkle-violet (#8b7ec8) and
muted teal (#5fd4c4).

Added two new themes with full parallel structure to the existing 8:
- Velvet: deep plum, dusty rose-mauve primary, warm gold-tan secondary
- Lagoon: deep teal, calm coastal blue secondary
Both register in themeIds/themeMeta and appear automatically in the
Settings picker (it maps over themeIds generically, no per-theme UI
code needed).

Stremio/Nuvio provider badges now use fixed colors (Badge variants
'stremio'/'nuvio') instead of --color-primary/--color-secondary,
which could end up nearly identical on themes like Ember - making the
two provider types indistinguishable at a glance. Purple = Stremio,
blue = Nuvio, consistent across every theme now.

Bump to 1.9.18, changelog entry added.
